\section{Data Cleaning and Processing Overview}

The preparation of the dataset followed a series of clearly defined steps:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Initial inspection \& Renaming:} Verbose labels such as \textit{Reference Area} were renamed to \textit{Country} for clarity.
    \item \textbf{Filtering by unit:} Rows where \textit{Units of measurement} was not "Number" were removed to ensure analytical consistency.
    \item \textbf{Type consistency:} Year and Enrolment columns were converted to integer and float types respectively.
    \item \textbf{Feature Engineering (Deriving Male Data):} A critical observation was that "Male" data was missing. We pivoted the dataset and calculated the missing column using the formula: $ \text{Male} = \text{All Genders} - \text{Female} $.
\end{itemize}

